snippet: Before he even departs for next week’s trip, President Obama is confronting the reality that in a land so freighted with symbolism, any place he chooses to visit, or not visit, can strike a nerve.
abstract: Itinerary for Pres Obama's first state visit to Israel includes several predictable stops, with several conspicuous exceptions, including his plan not to visit the Western Wall or Knesset; choices indicate careful orchestration of visit, which will be fraught with political symbolism.
lead_paragraph: Before he even departs for next week’s trip, President Obama is confronting the reality that in a land so freighted with symbolism, any place he chooses to visit, or not visit, can strike a nerve.

headline.main: Obama’s Israel Itinerary Includes Some Standard Stops, but Not Others
headline.print_headline: Obama’s Israel Itinerary Includes Some Standard Stops, but Not Others
